  <description type="morphology">Plants forming open colonies, 2–5(–7.5) dm; twigs green, slightly angled, pilose or hairy.  Leaves deciduous; blade green, elliptic, 23–62 × 10–36 mm, subcoriaceous, margins entire, surfaces densely hairy, eglandular abaxially.  Flowers: calyx green, glandular-hairy; corolla white, cylindric, 5–9 mm, (glandular-hairy); filaments hairy.  Berries black, 7–9 mm diam., hairy.  Seeds 3–9, ca. 1 mm.  2n = 48.</description>
